  3. **No "ONTOLOGY" Label Text:** Use class `class="wireframe-tag"` inside every card. It must display only the raw, lowercase ontology name (e.g., `herobanner`, `socialproof`).
  4. **Strict Vertical Sorting:** Compile code sections in the exact vertical order specified in `layout.vertical_order`.
  5. **Layout Geometry Compliance:** Write parent container grid columns, text alignment, and CTA alignments according to the specifications inside `layout.geometry_consensus`.
  6. **Unified Placeholder Syntax:** Use a clean, readable hybrid format of `[Element Type: Topic/Intent Example]` that establishes the wireframe's visual rhythm while giving copywriters clear direction.
     - *H1 Headline Example:* `<h1>[H1 Headline: 24/7 Digital Fall Alarm with Automatic Detection]</h1>`
     - *H2 Headline Example:* `<h2>[H2 Section Title: Technical Capabilities & Smart Device Features]</h2>`
     - *H3 Headline Example:* `<h3>[H3 Feature Title: Heavy Fall Acceleration Sensors]</h3>`
     - *H4 Headline Example:* `<h4>[H4 Subsection Title: Support Helplines]</h4>`
     - *Description Example:* `<p>[Description: Explain how the device works without landlines, highlighting automatic sensor triggers.]</p>`
     - *Button Example:* `<a href="#" class="btn-placeholder-primary">[Button: Choose Annual Saver Plan]</a>`
- **Completion Criteria:** Complete single-file code block fully rendered.
- **Next State:** Move to STATE 5.

**[STATE 5: COMPLETE]**
- **Action:** State "Wireframe generated successfully. Ready for next project." Do not ask further questions or include closing conversational filler.
